        <ArticleTitle>The history and value of face masks.</ArticleTitle>
        <Pagination>
          <StartPage>23</StartPage>
          <MedlinePgn>23</MedlinePgn>
        </Pagination>
        <ELocationID EIdType="pii" ValidYN="Y">23</ELocationID>
        <ELocationID EIdType="doi" ValidYN="Y">10.1186/s40001-020-00423-4</ELocationID>
        <Abstract>
          <AbstractText>In the human population, social contacts are a key for transmission of bacteria and viruses. The use of face masks seems to be critical to prevent the transmission of SARS-CoV-2 for the period, in which therapeutic interventions are lacking. In this review, we describe the history of masks from the middle age to modern times.</AbstractText>
        </Abstract>
